  .suite-strip { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1px; background: #2a2a2a; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; margin-top: 32px; }
  .suite-card { background: #161616; padding: 20px; text-align: center; }
  .suite-brand { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .suite-role { font-size: 11px; color: #666; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; }
  .suite-card.active { background: #1a0a0a; }
  .suite-card.active .suite-brand { color: var(--red); }
  .suite-card.active .suite-role { color: var(--red); }

  .problems-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 16px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .problem-card { border: 1px solid var(--border); background: #fff; padding: 20px; }
  .problem-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; color: var(--text); }
  .problem-cause { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .problem-tag { display: inline-block; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; padding: 3px 8px; color: #fff; }
  .tag-common { background: var(--red); }
  .tag-la { background: #2a5ea5; }
  .tag-urgent { background: #8b0000; }

  .pricing-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 24px; }
  .pricing-table th { background: var(--text); color: #fff; text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
  .pricing-table td { padding: 14px 16px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 14px; }
  .pricing-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .pricing-table tr:nth-child(even) td { background: var(--gray); }
  .price-range { font-weight: 700; color: var(--red); }

  .why-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 24px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .why-card { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); padding: 20px; background: #fff; }
  .why-icon { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .why-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .why-desc { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }

  .reviews-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .review-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 24px; }
  .review-stars { color: var(--red); font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .review-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .review-author { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted); }

  .repairs-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); margin-top: 32px; }
  .repair-item { background: #fff; padding: 24px; }
  .repair-appliance { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .repair-issue { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .repair-detail { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }
  .repair-meta { margin-top: 12px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: #aaa; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .faq-list { margin-top: 32px; }
  .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px 0; }
  .faq-q { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .faq-a { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; }

  .nearby-grid { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-top: 20px; }
  .nearby-chip { background: var(--gray); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 8px 14px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
  .nearby-chip:hover { border-color: var(--red); color: var(--red); }

  .bottom-cta { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px; text-align: center; color: #fff; }
  .bottom-cta-title { font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 44px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .bottom-cta-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .bottom-cta-sub { font-size: 17px; color: #888; margin-bottom: 32px; }
  .cta-phone-large { display: inline-block; font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 42px); font-weight: 900; color: #fff; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 24px; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--red); padding-bottom: 4px; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .hero-badge-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .features-2col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .suite-strip { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .trust-bar-inner { flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; }
  }
</style>

<!-- TOP BAR -->
<div class="top-bar">
  <span>Mon–Sat 8am–8pm · Los Angeles &amp; Southern California</span>
  <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`}>{phone}</a>
</div>

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div>
      <div class="hero-eyebrow">Cove Dishwasher Repair — Los Angeles</div>
      <h1 class="hero-title">
        Cove Repair.<br/>
        <span>The Quietest</span><br/>
        Fix in LA.
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Cove is the newest member of Sub-Zero Group — launched in 2019 specifically to match Wolf and Sub-Zero kitchens. We service all Cove models including panel-ready integrated units under custom cabinetry, same day, without damaging your millwork. Leaks treated as emergency calls.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-cta-group">
        <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`} class="btn-primary">Call {phone}</a>
        <a href="/book/" class="btn-secondary">Book Online</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-badge-grid">
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">Same</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Day Service</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">OEM</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Cove Parts</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">90-Day</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Warranty</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">$89</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Diagnostic Fee</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- TRUST BAR -->
<div class="trust-bar">
  <div class="trust-bar-inner">
    <span class="trust-item">Licensed &amp; Insured · CSLB #1138898</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Panel-Ready Installation Specialists</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Genuine Cove OEM Parts</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Wolf + Sub-Zero Suite Service</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Leaks — Emergency Same Day</span>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- 01 — ABOUT COVE -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">01 — About Cove</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">The Newest Member of Sub-Zero Group — Built for the Suite</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">
      Cove launched in 2019 as Sub-Zero Group's answer to a gap in their kitchen suite: they had the refrigerator (Sub-Zero), the cooking (Wolf), but no dishwasher to complete the package. Cove was built specifically to match the quality level and design language of Sub-Zero and Wolf — not adapted from an existing platform, but designed from scratch for luxury kitchen integration.
    </p>
    <p class="section-lead">
      The result is a dishwasher built around three things: silence (as low as 40 dBA — among the quietest residential dishwashers made), soil sensing that automatically adjusts wash intensity based on actual load contamination, and panel-ready design that lets it disappear completely into custom cabinetry. That panel-ready integration is also what makes Cove service calls different — pulling the machine for diagnosis requires knowing the mounting system and protecting the custom panel finish.
    </p>

    <div class="suite-strip">
      <div class="suite-card">
        <div class="suite-brand">Sub-Zero</div>
        <div class="suite-role">Refrigeration · Since 1945</div>
      </div>
      <div class="suite-card">
        <div class="suite-brand">Wolf</div>
        <div class="suite-role">Cooking · Since 1934</div>
      </div>
      <div class="suite-card active">
        <div class="suite-brand">Cove</div>
        <div class="suite-role">Dishwashing · Since 2019</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-block tip-urgent" style="margin-top:32px">
      <div class="tip-label">🚨 Cove Leak — Treat as Emergency</div>
      <div class="tip-text">Cove's leak detection pan is designed to capture water if the tub seal, door gasket, or pump housing leaks. In kitchens with hardwood or stone tile flooring — which covers most LA luxury kitchens — that pan can overflow within one or two cycles. If your Cove is showing a leak indicator, or you see water on the floor around the dishwasher, stop running it and call immediately. We prioritize Cove leak calls for same-day response.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 — SERVICES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">02 — Services</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Cove Dishwasher Issues We Repair</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">Same-day availability across Los Angeles County. We stock common Cove OEM parts on every truck.</p>

    <div class="services-grid">
      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🚿</div>
        <div class="service-name">Not Draining</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Standing water after a cycle is one of the most common Cove calls we receive in LA. The triple-filter system accumulates mineral deposits from hard water in addition to food particles — this reduces flow until the drain pump can't clear the tub. We clean the filter system, test the drain pump, and check the drain hose for kinks or clogs.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Causes: clogged fine filter · drain pump impeller · kinked drain hose · blocked air gap · drain solenoid · hard water mineral buildup in drain path</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🍽️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Not Cleaning Properly</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Dishes coming out with food residue or white film. In LA hard-water kitchens, this almost always traces to clogged spray arm nozzles (scale blocks the jets) or a mineral-coated filter reducing wash pressure. Cove's soil sensor can also give incorrect cycle parameters if dirty — we clean and test all three before ordering parts.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Causes: spray arm nozzles clogged · filter system scaled · soil sensor contaminated · low water pressure · water temperature · wash pump partially impaired</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">💧</div>
        <div class="service-name">Leaking</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Cove leaks are emergency calls. Water on the kitchen floor near a Cove dishwasher — or the leak indicator light on — means the leak detection pan has already activated. We diagnose the source (door gasket, tub seal, pump housing, water inlet), repair with OEM parts, and verify dry operation before leaving.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Sources: door gasket worn · tub seal · pump housing crack · water inlet valve · door spring misalignment · connection hose fitting</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🌬️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Not Drying</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Cove uses a condensation drying system — no exposed heating element. When drying performance drops, the cause is usually a failed rinse-aid dispenser (rinse aid is essential for condensation drying), a scaled heating element in the wash circuit affecting final rinse temperature, or a ventilation issue with the door.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Causes: rinse-aid dispenser failure · heating element scale · door vent restricted · wash temperature too low · final rinse sensor</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">⚡</div>
        <div class="service-name">Error Codes &amp; Control Issues</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Cove's smart display shows fault codes when the machine detects an issue. We read the full fault history — not just the current error — to identify root causes. Common codes relate to water intake, drain timing, soil sensor calibration, and door latch confirmation. Control board failures are less common but do occur on machines that have experienced water exposure.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common codes: water intake fault · drain timing · soil sensor · door latch · wash motor · heater circuit · control board</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🔇</div>
        <div class="service-name">Unusual Noise</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Cove is one of the quietest dishwashers made — any unusual noise is immediately obvious. Grinding usually means the wash pump impeller has debris; humming or vibration indicates a motor mount issue. We also check that the panel-ready door panel hasn't come loose, which can cause vibration resonance at certain cycle speeds.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Causes: pump impeller debris · loose motor mount · panel resonance · drain pump bearing · spray arm contact · circulation pump</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-block tip-blue" style="margin-top:32px">
      <div class="tip-label">💧 LA Hard Water and Your Cove</div>
      <div class="tip-text">Los Angeles water hardness runs 250–400 ppm depending on your district — significantly above the 7 gpg threshold where dishwasher mineral buildup accelerates. Cove's spray arm nozzles (small diameter precision jets) clog faster than standard dishwasher spray arms in hard-water conditions. Annual filter and spray arm service in LA prevents the majority of "not cleaning" calls we receive. We set the internal rinse-aid dispenser and water temperature to compensate for LA hardness on every service visit.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 — PANEL-READY EXPERTISE -->
<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">03 — Panel-Ready Service</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Cove Panel-Ready — Why It Requires a Specialist</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">Most Cove dishwashers in LA luxury kitchens are panel-ready models — designed to accept a custom cabinet panel so the dishwasher disappears into the kitchen design. Servicing them is different from standard dishwasher repair, and doing it wrong damages expensive custom cabinetry.</p>

    <div class="features-2col">
      <ul class="features-list">
        <li><strong>Panel Removal Without Damage</strong> — Cove's panel-ready design uses a specific mounting bracket and hinge system. The decorative panel must be removed before the unit can be pulled for diagnosis. We use the correct panel removal tools and protect the panel finish and hinge alignment during service.</li>
        <li><strong>Cabinetry Protection</strong> — Custom kitchen cabinetry in Beverly Hills, Brentwood, or Pacific Palisades can cost tens of thousands of dollars. We lay protective covers on adjacent cabinetry and flooring before pulling any panel-ready unit. Scratches from tool contact are preventable — we prevent them.</li>
        <li><strong>Correct Reinstallation</strong> — After service, the panel must be rehung at the correct height and level to align with adjacent cabinet doors. We verify alignment before leaving — an off-level panel is obvious in a well-designed kitchen and we don't leave it that way.</li>
        <li><strong>Leak Verification on Panel Units</strong> — Panel-ready units are harder to observe during a leak test because the panel conceals the door perimeter. We run a full leak test with the panel removed, verify dry operation, then reinstall and run a final cycle to confirm.</li>
      </ul>
      <div>
        <div class="tip-block" style="background:#0d1015; border-color:#3a7bd5; margin-top:0">
          <div class="tip-label" style="color:#6aabff">🔧 Soil Sensing Technology</div>
          <div class="tip-text" style="color:#bbb">Cove's soil sensor monitors water turbidity throughout the wash cycle and automatically extends or intensifies the wash if it detects heavy contamination. When the sensor fails or becomes coated with grease, the machine runs on a default cycle regardless of actual load — heavy items come out dirty, light loads run too long. We clean and test the soil sensor on every Cove service call as standard procedure.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tip-block tip-yellow" style="margin-top:16px">
          <div class="tip-label">⚙️ Post-Warranty Service</div>
          <div class="tip-text">Cove launched in 2019. Many LA machines are now 4–6 years old — either just past warranty or approaching it. Out-of-warranty Cove service doesn't have to go back to the manufacturer. We carry OEM Cove parts and service all models post-warranty with the same quality and parts as in-warranty service, at transparent flat-rate pricing.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
