<!-- 04 — COMMON PROBLEMS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">04 — Common Problems</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Most Common Cove Failures in Los Angeles</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">Cove is a relatively young brand — launched 2019 — and LA machines are now entering the period where first failures occur. Here's what we see most often.</p>

    <div class="problems-grid">
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🚿 Standing Water After Cycle (F-Drain)</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Clogged fine filter — the most common Cove call in LA. Hard water mineral deposits combine with food debris to block the triple-filter system. The drain pump can't overcome the restriction. Five-minute filter clean resolves it in most cases. We also check the drain pump impeller for debris and the drain hose for kinks.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-la">LA Hard Water</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🍽️ White Film on Glassware</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Hard water mineral deposits — calcium and magnesium on glass surfaces. This is a water chemistry issue, not a machine failure. We verify the rinse-aid dispenser is functioning correctly, check the internal water temperature setting, and advise on rinse-aid type and frequency for LA water hardness. Citric acid rinse cycle often resolves existing film.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-la">LA Hard Water</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">💧 Door Gasket Leak</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Door gasket compression failure — the most common source of Cove leaks. The gasket seals the door perimeter; when it loses elasticity or takes a compression set, the seal fails at the bottom corners first. On panel-ready units, this leak is invisible until water appears on the floor. We replace with OEM gasket and verify seal across the full door perimeter.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-urgent">Urgent</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔇 Grinding Noise Mid-Cycle</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Debris in the wash pump impeller — a bone fragment, glass chip, or hard seed that passed through the filter. Cove's pump is quieter than most, which makes impeller contact immediately obvious. We access the pump chamber, clear the debris, and inspect the impeller blades for damage before reassembling.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">⚡ Error Code at Cycle Start</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Water intake fault (most common) — usually a kinked water supply hose, a partially closed supply valve, or a scaled water inlet valve from hard water. We read the full fault history, not just the current code, before diagnosing. Water inlet valve replacement resolves most intake faults; control board is rarely the root cause.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🌬️ Dishes Not Drying</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Failed rinse-aid dispenser — Cove's condensation drying depends entirely on rinse aid creating a sheeting effect on dishes. When the dispenser solenoid fails, no rinse aid is released regardless of the reservoir level. Alternatively, a scaled heating element in the wash circuit reduces final rinse temperature, which also compromises drying.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

