        <div class="faq-a">White film on glassware is a hard water mineral deposit issue — almost universal in LA with 250–400 ppm water. Your Cove's rinse-aid dispenser needs to be set at maximum volume for LA conditions, and the spray arm nozzles likely need descaling. We address both on every service call. A citric acid maintenance cycle also helps clear existing deposits.</div>
